From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@example.com>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Map PicoCalc page and blit ids away from fbdev surfaces

The native fbdev path reserves internal surfaces 1, 2, and 3 for framebuffer
N/F/L. Existing PicoCalc compatibility tests still expect BASIC `PAGE 1` and
`BLIT READ 1` to be independent user-visible objects. After the fbdev switch,
those numeric IDs collided with the visible framebuffer surface.

Add a PicoCalc-only page mapping where BASIC page 0 is the visible N surface
and BASIC page 1..60 live in internal surfaces 4..63. Also map PicoCalc BLIT
IDs into the existing CMM2-style blit range 64..127. PAGE commands now parse
page IDs directly instead of forwarding to GRAPHICS raw-surface commands.
---
diff --git a/src/commands/cmd_blit.c b/src/commands/cmd_blit.c
index 30d42e2..6b87c24 100644
--- a/src/commands/cmd_blit.c
+++ b/src/commands/cmd_blit.c
@@ -69,11 +69,12 @@ static MmResult cmd_blit_close(const char *p) {
 static MmResult cmd_blit_close_all(const char *p) {
     skipspace(p);
     if (!parse_is_end(p)) return kUnexpectedText;
+    const bool picocalc = graphics_is_default_display_picocalc();
     MmResult result = kOk;
-    const MmSurfaceId start_id = (mmb_options.simulate == kSimulateMmb4l)
+    const MmSurfaceId start_id = (mmb_options.simulate == kSimulateMmb4l && !picocalc)
             ? 0
             : CMM2_BLIT_BASE + 1; // 64
-    const MmSurfaceId end_id = (mmb_options.simulate == kSimulateMmb4l)
+    const MmSurfaceId end_id = (mmb_options.simulate == kSimulateMmb4l && !picocalc)
             ? GRAPHICS_MAX_ID
             : CMM2_BLIT_BASE + CMM2_BLIT_COUNT; // 127
     for (MmSurfaceId surface_id = start_id; surface_id <= end_id; ++surface_id) {
